The course covers research areas and applications of applied anthropology and ethnographic method - principles, procedures and important aspects (e.g. research ethics). Participants of the course carry on research projects using observation and interviews.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides an overview of the research areas and methods of applied anthropology (with the main focus on business and organizational anthropology). The practical ethnographic research projects give hands-on experience and help to analyze and reflect on ethnographer's roles, methods and dilemmas with a further aim to be able to apply this approach in co-design processes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: *	Knows key concepts and approaches in anthropology (e.g. culture, practice, the Other, empathy) and is able to apply these in his/her research or work. *	Knows the basics about the subfields of applied anthropology (in the studies of organizations, target groups). *	Knows the principles of and has hands-on experience with participant observation and interviewing techniques. *	Is able to plan ethnographic study - knows where to find additional guidelines and literature for this purpose. *	Has basic knowledge of co-design method.
